Third-party content notices.

The validation corpus and worked-examples collection bundle verbatim
content from third parties under the following postures:

  - AI-generated content. Bundled corpus and worked-example assets
    include verbatim outputs from third-party AI providers (Anthropic
    Claude, OpenAI GPT, Google Gemini, xAI Grok). These outputs are
    redistributed in service of the methodology's transparency
    discipline (showing the documents Frame Check was measured on).
    Each provider's terms of service govern downstream redistribution
    of model outputs; consult the relevant provider's terms before
    redistributing the LLM-generated portions of the bundled assets.
    Primary location of AI-generated content:
    data/worked_examples/four-llms-on-bitcoin-retirement-2026/llm_responses.json
    and the eight derived corpus entries under
    validation/decision_readiness/corpus/four-llms-{bitcoin,startup}-{claude,gemini,grok,openai}/.

  - Press release content. The validation corpus bundles one verbatim
    third-party press release for transparency: NVIDIA Q4 FY24
    earnings (validation/decision_readiness/corpus/nvidia-q4-fy24-press-release/document.md).
    Copyright remains with NVIDIA Corporation; the document is
    redistributed under standard fair-use posture for analytical
    excerpting in research and methodology demonstration. Frame
    Check's analytical commentary on the press release is CC-BY-4.0;
    the press release text itself is not.

Frame Check's analytical outputs (measurements, profiles, frame matches,
narrative interpretations) over any input — including third-party content
above — are CC-BY-4.0 as part of the methodology's transparency posture.
